# Mirrors the root .terminology-forbidden (deeper files REPLACE shallower
# per scripts/lint-terminology.sh, so root patterns must be copied here to
# stay in force for docs/). The docs-only additions live below the root
# block. Keep in sync with the root file when root patterns change; add
# docs-only patterns under §Doc-only below.
#
# Scope note: this file is docs/-scoped (not root) so the .working/
# catalogues that legitimately quote superseded vocabulary don't
# false-positive; root scope continues to govern them.

# === Removed primitives (post-kels#214 simplification) ===
# Cnt removed; per-node Contested removed; upgrade rule removed.
\bCnt\b
\bis_contested\b
\bupgrade[ _]rule\b

# === Removed identifiers (post-kels#218 federation trust model) ===
# Static trusted prefix list replaced with federation Fcp SAID set.
\bTRUSTED_REGISTRY_PREFIXES\b
\bTRUSTED_REGISTRY_MEMBERS\b

# === Rejected design directions (post-kels#218) ===
# Federation-Dip / Fip ruled out — federation IEL uses Fcp self-signing carve-out.
\bFederation-Dip\b
\bFip\b

# === Renamed services (kels consolidation) ===
# sadstore + kels-service consolidated into vdtid; gossip-service → witnessd.
\bsadstore\b
\bkels-service\b
\bgossip-service\b
\bkels-sadstore\b

# === kels-internal tool / agent names (out-of-context in vdti) ===
# Distinctive enough to forbid; common words ("max", "min") rely on review.
\bclaudit\b
\bxhigh\b

# === kels protocol namespace leakage ===
# vdti has its own namespace: vdti/witness/v1/topics/*, vdti/sad/v1/*, etc.
kels/gossip/
kels/witness/
kels/sad/

