# === Old policy-DSL leaf / composer names ===
# The policy language: leaves id (identity) / del (delegate), reference pol;
# composers thr / wgt / and. (dev and grp are dropped — forbidden in the
# log-primitive reshape block below.) Forbidden here = every superseded spelling:
#   pre-vdti:   Endorse( → (dropped) ; Delegate( → del( ; identity( → id( ;
#               threshold( → thr( ; Weighted → wgt ; nested Policy( → pol.
#   vdti log-names (the DSL surface speaks identity/delegate, not log type):
#               iel( → id( ; kel( → (dropped) ; mem( → (dropped).
# Call-form (trailing "(") so the uppercase IEL/KEL/SEL primitives and the
# kel/ // iel/ doc paths are NOT matched.
\bEndorse\(
\bDelegate\(
\bidentity\(
\bthreshold\(
\bWeighted\b
\bPolicy\(
\biel\(
\bkel\(
\bmem\(

# === Superseded SEL prefix tuples ===
# Settled tuple is (governance, operation, topic).
\(identity,[[:space:]]*topic\)
\(governance,[[:space:]]*topic\)

# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — pre-policyPin field names
# ============================================================================
# ielEvent / ielPrefix / policyBinding / "binding SAD" are superseded spellings;
# no such field exists. (Their one-time successors policyPin and
# federationBinding are THEMSELVES superseded by the log-primitive reshape —
# forbidden in the reshape block below.) \bielEvent\b does not match custody's
# ownerIelEvent (case differs at the boundary).
\bielEvent\b
\bielPrefix\b
\bpolicyBinding\b
[bB]inding[ -]SAD

# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — log-primitive reshape superseded vocabulary
# ============================================================================
# The log-primitive reshape moved policy off the chain primitives onto documents
# and resettled the event taxonomy. These pre-reshape tokens must not regress
# into docs:
#   IEL evolve event Evl → Gov (roster/threshold change only);
#   SEL Est removed (a credential SEL's pin rides in its data; a lookup SEL
#     carries a Pin event);
#   IEL Rsc-as-an-event removed (rescission is a derived lookup SEL);
#   SEL policyPin removed (chain events carry no policy; a SEL floors up via its
#     pin / data);
#   KEL federationBinding → federation (prefix) + federationPin (SAID);
#   policy-DSL leaves dev() / grp() dropped (identity composition is thr / wgt /
#     and over id()). Call-form ("(") so device/develop/group are not matched.
\bEvl\b
\bEst\b
\bRsc\b
\bpolicyPin\b
\bfederationBinding\b
\bdev\(
\bgrp\(
# The 3-function policy evaluator (gate / anchored / current) collapsed to two
# modes (as-issued / current) sharing one composer; all the old function names —
# including the earlier evaluate_single_policy — are retired. The interim
# 2-function name evaluate_anchored was renamed to evaluate_as_issued (the mode
# is "as-issued"; "anchored" stays the structural verb — manifest anchors, the
# anchoring position — so only the evaluate_ form is forbidden):
\bevaluate_gate_policy\b
\bevaluate_anchored_policy\b
\bevaluate_current_policy\b
\bevaluate_single_policy\b
\bevaluate_anchored\b

# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — seal-cap rejection error name (SiblingLocked, not ParentLocked)
# ============================================================================
# The seal-cap rejection is SiblingLocked — the candidate would sibling a
# locked event. There is no ParentLocked error: a parent AT the seal is
# extendable (parent_serial == seal_serial passes the cap), so "parent locked"
# is not a rejection condition.
\bParentLocked\b
